  "text": "Unfortunately, due to the low number of samples (n = 8), a detailed analysis of the data validity using DOC measurements was difficult at SATURN-05. For the available data, no significant correlation between in situ FDOM readings and DOC was found. This was also true when considering the extended dataset of in situ FDOM and DOC (measured by USGS) 25 between 2009 and 2013. Therefore, the differences in readings between SATURN-05 and SATURN-08 are likely caused by one or several disturbances. Firstly, instrumental issues could have affected readings at SATURN-05. However, it has to be noted that samples discussed in [CITATION_1] were taken at the same location and DOC was also found to be not well ",
